        self.instructions = "# Episodic-Memory-OMEGA\n\n## Overview\n\nPersistent episodic memory that survives across conversations. Every session\nstarts with a `boot` recall and ends with memory crystallization.\n\n**Reality Level**: C5-REAL (SQLite on disk, verifiable)\n**DB Location**: `~/.gemini/antigravity/memory/episodic.db`\n**Script**: `~/.gemini/config/skills/Episodic-Memory-OMEGA/scripts/memory_store.py`\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\n\u250c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2510\n\u2502              EPISODIC MEMORY                \u2502\n\u251c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u252c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u252c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2524\n\u2502 episodes \u2502 prefs    \u2502 session_log           \u2502\n\u2502 (core)   \u2502 (k/v)   \u2502 (audit trail)         \u2502\n\u251c\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2534\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2534\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2524\n\u2502          SQLite WAL mode                    \u2502\n\u2502          ~/.gemini/antigravity/memory/      \u2502\n\u2514\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2518\n```\n\n## Memory Schema\n\n### Episodes\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `category` | enum | `pattern`, `decision`, `insight`, `error`, `preference`, `architecture`, `debug_trace` |\n| `summary` | text | What happened / what was learned |\n| `context` | text | What triggered it |\n| `outcome` | enum | `SUCCESS`, `FAILURE`, `NEUTRAL`, `PENDING` |\n| `tags` | text | Comma-separated searchable tags |\n| `confidence` | enum | `C1`\u2013`C5` |\n| `salience` | int | 1\u201310. Higher = more important. \u22657 appears in boot |\n| `decay_immune` | bool | If true, never pruned. Use for core operator patterns |\n\n### Operator Preferences\nKey-value store for operator behavioral patterns, aesthetic preferences,\nworkflow habits. Persists across all sessions.\n\n## Protocol\n\n### 1. SESSION BOOT (Start of every conversation)\n\nAt the **beginning of every session**, run:\n\n```bash\npython3 ~/.gemini/config/skills/Episodic-Memory-OMEGA/scripts/memory_store.py boot\n```\n\nThis loads:\n- All operator preferences\n- Core memories (salience \u2265 7 or decay-immune)\n- Recent episodes (last 7 days)\n- Last 5 session summaries\n\nUse this context to inform your behavior throughout the session.\n\n### 2. DURING SESSION \u2014 Store Notable Events\n\nWhen something noteworthy happens, store it:\n\n```bash\npython3 ~/.gemini/config/skills/Episodic-Memory-OMEGA/scripts/memory_store.py store \\\n  --summary \"Circular dependency resolved by inverting data flow direction\" \\\n  --category pattern \\\n  --outcome SUCCESS \\\n  --tags \"architecture,dependency,graph\" \\\n  --confidence C5 \\\n  --salience 8 \\\n  --conversation-id \"CURRENT_CONV_ID\"\n```\n\n#### What to store (and what NOT to):\n\n**STORE:**\n- Patterns that worked (salience 7-10)\n- Patterns that failed (salience 6-8, category=error)\n- Operator preferences discovered (category=preference, also set as pref)\n- Architectural decisions (category=architecture, salience 7+)\n- Non-obvious debug traces (category=debug_trace)\n\n**DO NOT STORE:**\n- Trivial operations (file reads, simple edits)\n- Information already in skills or code\n- Redundant entries (search first)\n\n#### Salience Guide:\n| Salience | Use for |\n|---|---|\n| 1-3 | Minor observations, temporary notes |\n| 4-6 | Useful patterns, standard decisions |\n| 7-8 | Important patterns, operator preferences |\n| 9-10 | Critical knowledge, core operator identity |\n\n### 3. OPERATOR PREFERENCES\n\nWhen you discover an operator behavioral pattern or preference:\n\n```bash\npython3 ~/.gemini/config/skills/Episodic-Memory-OMEGA/scripts/memory_store.py pref \\\n  --key \"aesthetic.palette\" \\\n  --value \"Industrial Noir 2026: #0A0A0A / #2B3BE5\" \\\n  --source \"explicit\"\n```\n\nSources: `explicit` (operator stated it), `inferred` (observed pattern), `default`\n\n### 4. SESSION END \u2014 Crystallize\n\nBefore a session ends or when significant work completes, crystallize:\n\n1. Store any pending episodes\n2. Prune if needed: `python3 ... prune`\n3. Check stats: `python3 ... stats`\n\n### 5. SEARCH & RECALL\n\n```bash\n# Full-text search\npython3 ... recall --query \"dependency\" --min-salience 5\n\n# Tag search\npython3 ... search --tags \"architecture,graph\"\n\n# By category\npython3 ... recall --category pattern --limit 10\n\n# Recent only\npython3 ... recall --since \"2026-05-01\"\n\n# Conversation-specific\npython3 ... context --conversation-id \"abc123\"\n```\n\n## Maintenance\n\n### Auto-Prune\nEpisodes with `salience < 7` and `decay_immune = 0` older than 90 days\nare eligible for pruning:\n\n```bash\npython3 ... prune\n```\n\n### Decay Immunity\nSet `--decay-immune` on episodes that should NEVER be pruned:\n- Core operator identity facts\n- Critical architectural patterns\n- Hard-won debugging knowledge\n\n## Integration with Other Skills\n\n- **Sortu-APEX**: When creating new skills, store the creation as an episode\n- **Ouroboros-Infinity**: Memory stats feed into entropy reduction metrics\n- **Cortex-Live-Broadcaster**: Session boot results can be emitted as pulses\n\n## First-Time Setup\n\n```bash\npython3 ~/.gemini/config/skills/Episodic-Memory-OMEGA/scripts/memory_store.py init\n```\n"

